By the King where at the late session of our Parliament of this our realme of England, one act is made authorizing certaine persons of both Houses to assemble ... England and Wales. Sovereign (1603-1625 : James I) James I, King of England, 1566-1625.
1 sheet ([1] p.).
By Robert Barker, Printer to the Kings most Excellent Maiestie, Imprinted at London : Anno Dom. 1604.
Appointing 20 Oct. as the meeting day for the Commissioners for the Union to meet. Other title information from first 3 lines of text. "Giuen at our Castel of Windsor the fifteenth day of September in the second yeere of our Raigne of England, France and Ireland, and of Scotland the eight and thirtieth." Reproduction of original in: Society of Antiquaries.
